Minister for Public Service and Administration, Senzo Mchunu, will brief media on progress of readiness of the public service operations under the COVID-19 level 4 lockdown. Editor's note: This livestream has ended, you can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Minister for Public Service and Administration, Senzo Mchunu, briefed the media on the readiness of the public service operations under the COVID-19 level 4 lockdown. The Public Servants Association has raised concerns about some departments' readiness in dealing with employees returning to work. Government has eased some lockdown regulations to allow the economy to thrive. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.